Afrobeats songstress, Tiwa Savage has been unveiled as latest brand ambassador for a popular smartphone brand. Before her official unveiling, the smartphone had teased its followers to guess who their latest ambassador by sharing a foggy image of the singer. Officially welcoming her to their fold via its Instagram, as their ambassador for ‘Camon19Launch’, Tecnomobileng wrote: “Queen of Afrobeats! Mama Africa! Multitalented singer! Superstar extraordinaire and TECNO Ambassador, #TECNOxTiwaSavage. “Happy to have you @Tiwasavage as part of the family. #TECNOAmbassador #CAMON19Launch.”   Worst experience with someone I dated – Nedu     Kelly Hansome: My problem began after Timaya introduced me…     There are no roles that I cannot accept, Chioma Blessing   Confirming the news in the comment section, the “Koroba” singer wrote: “The sexiest phone ever.” Taking to her social media pages, Tiwa announced to her fans that she is the newest brand ambassador for smartphones. Sharing an advert snippet of the brand, Tiwa wrote: “This one is highly approved by the No1ABG, Your girl is on board with one of the coolest brands ever – TECNO! “Head over to @tecnomobileng and show some love to my newest family. I am sooooo excited. #TECNOxTiwaSavage #TECNOAmbassador.”